        "title": "How to open up device credential check using a Biometric Prompt?",
        "body": "<p>I got an application where users can choose to login using their fingerprint or the given device credential (pin etc.) after their first login. The fingerprint part is working fine using a <code>new BiometricPrompt.PromptInfo.Builder()<\/code> and some given title and negative button for cancelling. Now I would like to make another part for device credential check, when the user has chosen this login method in the app. So I have added <code>.setDeviceCredentialAllowed(true)<\/code> to the <code>BiometricPrompt.PromptInfo.Builder()<\/code> (which shows a &quot;Use PIN&quot; -button for fallback instead of Cancel -button).<\/p>\n<p>Is it possible to disable the fingerprint part and get access to &quot;Use PIN&quot; -button immediately so that the user can authenticate using their PIN?<\/p>\n",
